{"id":22,"category_slug":"short-stories","category_name":"Short Stories","position":14,"title":"14. Remembrance Day","subtitle":"","level":"A2","parts":15,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/short-stories/14-remembrance-day.22/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/0-14-remembrance-day.mp3","transcript":"My grandfather fought in World War II.\nMy grandmother was a nurse in World War II.\nToday is November 11th.\nToday is Remembrance Day.\nToday we celebrate soldiers.\nEveryone wears a poppy.\nPoppies are red flowers.\nPoppies remind me of my grandparents.\nPoppies remind me of their sacrifice.\nAt 11 A.M, there are two minutes of silence.\nPeople remember their friends and family.\nPeople recite the poem \"In Flanders Field\".\nIt is a sad poem.\nIt helps us remember.\nToday we wish for peace in the world.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:55:29","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"My grandfather fought in World War II.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/1.mp3","time_start":2.8,"time_end":5.64},{"position":2,"content":"My grandmother was a nurse in World War II.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/2.mp3","time_start":6.1,"time_end":9.47},{"position":3,"content":"Today is November 11th.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/3.mp3","time_start":10.0,"time_end":12.3},{"position":4,"content":"Today is Remembrance Day.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/4.mp3","time_start":12.7,"time_end":14.83},{"position":5,"content":"Today we celebrate soldiers.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/5.mp3","time_start":15.5,"time_end":17.8},{"position":6,"content":"Everyone wears a poppy.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/6.mp3","time_start":18.3,"time_end":20.24},{"position":7,"content":"Poppies are red flowers.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/7.mp3","time_start":20.8,"time_end":22.95},{"position":8,"content":"Poppies remind me of my grandparents.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/8.mp3","time_start":23.6,"time_end":26.24},{"position":9,"content":"Poppies remind me of their sacrifice.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/9.mp3","time_start":26.8,"time_end":29.49},{"position":10,"content":"At 11 A.M, there are two minutes of silence.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/10.mp3","time_start":30.26,"time_end":33.96},{"position":11,"content":"People remember their friends and family.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/11.mp3","time_start":34.6,"time_end":37.25},{"position":12,"content":"People recite the poem \"In Flanders Field\".","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/12.mp3","time_start":37.88,"time_end":41.42},{"position":13,"content":"It is a sad poem.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/13.mp3","time_start":41.9,"time_end":43.5},{"position":14,"content":"It helps us remember.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/14.mp3","time_start":43.79,"time_end":45.28},{"position":15,"content":"Today we wish for peace in the world.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/general-english/14-remembrance-day-2019-03-20-04-52-03/15.mp3","time_start":45.9,"time_end":48.63}]}